HOUSE UPDATE /// This first clip is what our current kitchen that we are living with. The last one is our before video when we saw it for the first time with our realtor @ginnyelee . 

There is so much that we want to do but I want to make sure that we make the right choices for us and we are trying to decide what is priority.

I am enjoying this phase and want to remember every step of the way. I am in love with our floors and they are exactly what we wanted. I love an undone look and I still want our kitchen to have that whole undone vibe we are just trying to figure out the layout right now and we want to live in it a little longer so we really know what we need. 

We currently use a hot plate in place of a stove top. We still have an oven, micro wave, and instapot. A popular question is where do we keep our food if our pantry has our dishes in it. 
Our food is stored in our bottom cabinets in bins. Our last place didn’t have a huge pantry so we got used to not storing so much and it works for us bc we just shop every couple days. 

So the question we keep asking ourselves is do we want one big kitchen space with our table or do we want to have a kitchen area and separate dining area?

Going to work / running errands outfit rules /// 
1. Must be comfy 
2. Can’t care too much if I stain with hair color
3. I have to feel my kinda stylish

I Definitely got dark color on denim shirt but it’s thrifted and I’m pretty sure I can get this out.

We woke up and went running in the cold until my skin got itchy then we walked, took the dogs on an extra long walk after and we found our white elephant gifts today 🙌🏼 and it was chilly outside and we ate tacos and we thrifted and and we made it early to @worthyoflovehtown EARLY today. Gosh it was a good day and I’m so thankful for the days with Dante. Oh yeah and from now on I wanna write how I write in my morning pages at least for this post bc it’s fun. 

What have been you favorite white elephant gifts? Our family does the kind that you actually like not the gag kind.

COATS IN OUR CLOSET /// Day 1 
I wonder how many days of coat weather we are gonna get? I’ll take as many as we can because we never get to wear all our coats and they are my favorite. When the dogs saw us put our jackets and shoes on they started going crazy because they know that means WALK time! We have to be very careful when we say the W word around here. 

Harvey girl always with her timing 😂

My Coat 🧥 is thrifted I love the shape, color and hood. 
His Coat 🧥 he got his in London on a trip in 2000. It’s a staple.

COATS IN OUR CLOSET /// Day 2 
Is it time to bring our plant babies in yet? What temperature do you bring your succulents, pencil plants, and plumeria in? I’m a little paranoid since I’ve had some casualties before.

My 🧥 /// Botany 500 Thrifted. I love how oversized it is so that I can layer but it’s not too oversized. You can pretty much wear anything underneath a trench and look put together. 

His Blazer /// Thrfited Liz Claiborne. He’s giving me Miami Vice Vibes. 

I had to throw in my new @hmerrick shades because I haven’t stopped wearing them since they arrived at my door. The feel good on my face, don’t slide around, and I think they are super chic.  I’m very picky about sunnies because of my cheeks and how they feel when I smile in them. Anyone else in the chubby cheek club feel me?

Pipes are wrapped, plants are in, hoping everyone stays warm and cozy tonight. 

Decided it’s the perfect night to rewatch Beverly Hills 90210. Dante’s never watched the early seasons so I’m very excited. 

Dylan was my favorite 🤩 who was your favorite?

Merry Christmas Everyone ❤️🎄

We are cheesing it up over here watching all the new holiday movies and eating my moms yummy casseroles. This is the one thing that has stayed our constant in a life that is full of changes. I’m also very happy that Zeyk still chooses to come over to my lap for cuddles. It’s the little things y’all.

What are you excited for?

Have you tried listing 20 things you enjoy doing lately? It was part of my homework in this book I’m reading thanks to @kendallhanna and @iheartbueno . It was really easy to write down but then I thought about conversations I have with people and when you ask someone what they like/ enjoy doing a lot of times they go blank or maybe they don’t feel comfortable sharing or maybe they think I don’t really want to know… but I do! I want to know all the things. 

I wrote my list down and then I asked Dante if he could name some things I enjoy and he nailed every single one plus some more. 

Long walks around the neighborhood 
Cuddling my dogs
Riding bikes 
Listening to music and really connecting to it
Dancing like an idiot with my whole body
Deep conversations

The whole point for this assignment is to make sure your actually doing the things on your list and often. 

I hope you join in on the 20 things list. Feel free to share in comments or keep to yourself but when you share you inspire and you might just help someone remember something they used to love.

What makes you pick pieces for your home? Is it a feeling you get when you see it? Is it what you’ve seen your friends get, nostalgia, is it what’s popular at the moment, what your interior designer picked out, do you have specific things your hunting down, was it passed down to you, or is it just what was at the store you went to? 

I love when people have a back story or explain their home choices in home tours. 

A pommel horse in our entryway doesn’t exactly make sense but it’s art to us. The worn leather, the wood, the history, the sweat and hard work that it wears. It’s beautiful. I love the conversations that it starts or the weird looks people make before they ask about it. It was the feeling for me when I saw it.

Camp Champs at Garner State Park /// the first night was perfect, we had the whole site to ourselves probably because people feared it would rain. But instead we got to watch the most epic lightning storm from the cliffs behind our campsite. I’m sure @iheartbueno will post it soon. Thanks for making us get out of our comfy seats around the fire to go watch the show @corbin.christopher. Always an adventure with these guys. 🏕️🤟🏼🌎✌🏼🫶🏽 Dante asked why do you think we keep doing this? (Hiking) what makes us love it? 
I said because my mind gets to wander, you get to cheer yourself on to keep going, the challenge, the funny things that randomly pop up, talk to God, the songs we sing ( commercials from childhood) , people you think of, you get to work things out that you may have pushed out, you can be quiet, and you get to create these beautiful times with people you love.

FROM GYM 👉🏼 TO WORK @doordyetx /// 
1. ALWAYS USE HEAT PROTECTANT!!! Not yelling at you just yelling it loud because this is the most crucial thing you can do for your hair even if your not blowdrying or using hot tools because environment plays a factor too. Without it you are slowly melting your hair, and burning it off. We don’t skip our SPF on our face so we can’t skip HEATED.DEFENSE @kevin.murphy 
2. I just add some BENDS, S WAVES, or BARELY THERE waves on random strands, I don’t do entire head. 
3. I need all the volume help I can get so today I chose @oligopro DRY TEXTURE spray (we are having a promo with this) but two liters of oligo and get any oligo sprat FREE. 

For reference I washed my hair last night but worked out to a full sweat this morning. I waited until my hair naturally dried. Notice how I put HEATED.DEFENSE on my dry hair then blew the product dry? You don’t want to curl, flat iron or use any iron on damp hair at all 💀🙅🏽‍♀️ MUST BE COMPLETELY DRY 👍🏻

ROUND TOP /// Part 1 
There’s no wrong way to do it. Some people go to sell, some people go to dress the part and go to all the events, some people host, some people live and work there, some people are on a serious hunt, some people just want something to do, some people go for inspiration, some people just want an excuse for a girls trip. It’s all wonderful things. I mean the list goes on. I’m here for the hunt, the inspo, and the people watching. 

My Tips /// 
Stay hydrated 
Wear sunscreen 
Wear a 🧢 and sunglasses 
Hands free. (Cross body or Fanny pack) 
Wear comfortable 👟 
Bring a protein bar with you. 
Take a break drink more water. 
If you are seriously going for shopping and hunting don’t go with friends. I mean you can but just meet them for breakfast or at the end of the day bc it will slow you down or be distracting. I like to go at my pace. Sometimes slow to look at every little thing or sometimes I’m just taking a quick look while walking at a fast pace.

Which way do you like to Roundtop? Did you go at all this year? Any good finds?

Trying on clothes in your closet before a big purge. There is so much in there that just doesn’t feel like me anymore. I feel most like me when I have something OVERSIZED on. When I’m COMFORTABLE. And I prefer MORE MASCULINE items than Feminine. 

What about you? When getting ready what is your recipe to feeling like you?

My name is Brandi 

I am a hairstylist and co owner of @doordyetx 
I’ve been doing hair well over 20 years now.
If I didn’t choose this career I probably would be doing something in interior design. I love fashion and I was going that direction one time but I get more instant gratification in hair and people. 

My favorite place to be is at home with Dante and my 3 Dogs. It’s just so peaceful. 

I do love to entertain every once in awhile so I can create a special environment for my guests. 

It’s crazy how much you change over the years. I used to be so social and my schedule was packed, and I was traveling all the time but now I prefer a slower paced life, time at home so I can recharge, and really have time with my thoughts. I still love to be social but my job gives me a lot of that already. So being intentional with plans is important so people don’t just get tired or worn out Brandi. 

Finding recipes for us to try is one of my favorite pastimes along with home tours on you tube. This is my Sunday morning routine. 

I love creating all types of things. Art days at home are some of my favorite thing to do. I guess the reason I was doing this post was to introduce myself to new followers and check in with my old friends who have been following since the beginning bc a lot has changed over the years so thanks for sticking by me. Just curious if your still reading this, what is your favorite thing that I post ? Outfits, home stuff, things I eat, places I go, treasures I find?

I have a special place in my heart for social media bc I’ve found some of my best friends on here. It’s like online dating for friends.

It’s that time again… getting excited to have my family over for Thanksgiving. Wondering how I’m going to set the table this year. As of right now we will have 17 loved ones gathering to feast! I’ll prob set it up differently than last year.  I asked y’all in stories what your favorite side was because it’s always good to know what people want. Stuffing was a very popular answer. How do y’all make your stuffing? 
My favorite side is all of it mixed together! 
And left overs for days. But the broccoli cheese and rice casserole from my childhood is what I look forward to along with my families cheese enchiladas. I know it’s not a typical thanksgiving food but for us it is and makes me all sentimental.

THRIFT TIPS /// 
1. Find out the discount days at the thrift stores you want to check out. @valuevillagetx will send texts 👌🏼 @goodwillhouston puts colored tags with discounts on certain days. 
2. It helps when you already know what your looking for bc it can get overwhelming. Go to your Pinterest boards and try and find the looks you saved. 
3. MENS SECTION is a Gold Mine. 
4. Go when they first open and go often because they constantly get donations. 
5. Wash items immediately!!! Hang dry outside in sun. 
6. Wear clothing that you can easily try stuff over because lines can be long or some thrift stores don’t have dressing rooms. 

People always ask how I find such good stuff. It’s hit or miss honestly. I have to be in the mood and I always hit up the same sections.
